About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Luggage that Lasts and GREAT Customer Support
reviews.reviewText: I bought this luggage back in 2016. It has been on many trips since then and received a lot of abuse. After almost 7 years of use the wheels finally needed to be replaced. I contacted customer service for the replacement and they sent me 2 free wheels! It was so easy to take off and put the new ones on. I HIGHLY recommend this luggage. It's light, reliable and has an awesome team behind them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Took these to Hawaii, both were checked, held up great ! Very happy for the price ! Love the color too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice looking decently sturdy suitcases
reviews.reviewText: These suitcases look pretty darn good. The color is unique making them easy to spot at the airport. The handles actually feel strong enough to carry even the big suitcase with 50lbs of stuff in it and the wheels are great.My only issue is that the shell feels a little flimsy, though it has held up perfectly for two flights and a road trip. It just wobbles a bit as you are opening and closing the big suitcase. For the occasional traveler (a couple times a year or so) I think this set will absolutely hold up for years and be what you need without shelling out several hundred dollars. For a frequent traveler I would not expect it to last more than a year or two.

reviews.reviewText: I'm pleasantly surprised and pleased with this hardsided luggage. I ordered it in purple and they are a beautiful color. I'm looking forward to using them for an upcoming trip. I hope they hold up to the rough treatment airlines give luggage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Luggage was perfect...until I actually used it!
reviews.reviewText: I bought these in June for an August trip (past the 30 day return window), they had decent reviews & seemed like a good price. Having issues with previous brands rolling really well in the store but then not when they are full, I immediately put some weight in them & rolled them around my house on various flooring types as to not be fooled again and they were great, I was very happy. I set out on my trip & was pleased with their maneuverability through the airport! Baggage claim proved successful & I was off to my cruisetour that included a short small flight a couple days in. Once I received my luggage in my room that evening I noticed a tear near one of the wheels & was disappointed that I would have to return once back.. Next stop was worse, no surprise, but by the next stop 2 more wheels were all but completely torn off & rendered unrollable! Had it not been for my cabin steward who found me a whole roll of packing tape which I incased the bag in for my trip home allowing me to drag it through the airport, I'm not sure what I would have done & certainly my unmentionables would have been strewn all over the tarmac & luggage claim area! One of the reasons I felt safe purchasing was the 5 yr warranty that came with the bag. What a joke! A warranty that doesn't cover "damage by the common carrier" & costs you a $40 handling fee for the company to provide a "warranty evaluation"??? I think we all know how that would play out! Luckily Amazon is the best! A customer service rep was able to waive the return fee & refund my purchase for all but the $28 that Rockland will charge them for a "restocking fee". It cost me $28 & a big headache on my trip but at least I didn't have to pay $40, ship the bag back only to have Rockland determine it was "the common carrier's" fault & give me nothing! if you look through the questions asked section, you will see lots of pictures that look just like mine....So it's not an uncommon problem. Buyer Beware if you actually plan on using these.....
